---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import portrait from '@/assets/portrait/ahmed-hamdy-portrait-approved.webp';
import { site, withBase } from '@config/site';
---

<BaseLayout title={`About — ${site.name}`} description="The career story behind Ahmed Hamdy's work across customer experience, support operations, process improvement and business operations." path="/about">
  <section class="page-hero about-hero"><div class="wrap about-hero__grid"><div class="reveal is-visible"><span class="eyebrow">About Ahmed</span><h1>I learned to read the business from the point where customers feel it.</h1><p class="page-hero__copy">That customer-facing foundation did not disappear when my work moved deeper into operations and business improvement. It became the evidence base I still use.</p></div><div class="about-portrait reveal is-visible"><Image src={portrait} alt="Ahmed Hamdy" widths={[360,540,720]} sizes="(max-width:760px) 75vw, 340px" loading="eager" /><span>Alexandria, Egypt · Remote experience with a UK company</span></div></div></section>

  <section class="section zone-paper story-section"><div class="wrap story-grid"><div class="story-copy reveal"><span class="eyebrow">The short version</span><h2>Close customer exposure became operating judgment.</h2><p>Working through thousands of individual customer moments teaches a distinction that a report cannot: the difference between one unhappy customer and a process that will keep producing unhappy customers.</p><p>I began paying attention to what repeated—the same question, the same hesitation, the same escalation, the same point where a handoff failed. That changed the way I looked at support. The queue was not only work to complete; it was evidence about onboarding, content, policy, trust, product decisions and operations.</p><p>At Alpha Capital Group, that foundation developed inside a remote UK fintech environment and led to progression from Customer Support Specialist to Customer Manager after two years. In parallel, I kept applying the same system view to small businesses, commercial journeys and founder-led work.</p><p>Formula4You extended the responsibility. I had to turn a market gap into participant journeys, trust rules, operating decisions, platform requirements and a live specialist business. It showed me what happens after the diagnosis: priorities meet constraints, and every new idea creates work someone must own.</p></div><aside class="story-principle reveal reveal-delay-1"><blockquote>“When the same question keeps returning, the customer is often pointing at a part of the business they cannot name.”</blockquote><p>That is the thread running through my work today: customer experience, team performance, operating processes and business decisions are parts of one system.</p></aside></div></section>

  <section class="section timeline-section"><div class="wrap"><header class="section-head reveal"><div><span class="eyebrow">Career through-line</span><h2>The role expanded. The operating question stayed consistent.</h2></div><p>What is making the customer or team work harder than they should—and what part of the system needs to change?</p></header><div class="timeline"><article class="reveal"><span>Foundation</span><h3>Customer-facing work</h3><p>Communication, trust, difficult cases and the discipline of understanding what a customer is really asking.</p></article><article class="reveal"><span>Progression</span><h3>Alpha Capital Group</h3><p>High-volume Arabic and English customer work, recurring-pattern analysis, service quality, case guidance and progression to Customer Manager.</p></article><article class="reveal"><span>Professional direction</span><h3>Business Growth &amp; Operations</h3><p>Process improvement, customer-led decisions, service design, workflow clarity and coordination across company functions.</p></article><article class="reveal"><span>Founder ownership</span><h3>Formula4You</h3><p>Market diagnosis, participant journeys, platform operations, requirements and the responsibility of turning decisions into live work.</p></article></div></div></section>

  <section class="section zone-paper principles-section"><div class="wrap"><header class="section-head reveal"><div><span class="eyebrow">Working principles</span><h2>The standards I use when the answer is not obvious.</h2></div></header><div class="principle-grid"><article><span>01</span><h3>Do not punish the employee for a broken system.</h3><p>Check the guidance, policy, tools, workload and handoff before treating inconsistency as a motivation problem.</p></article><article><span>02</span><h3>Do not buy more demand for a journey that cannot convert it.</h3><p>Improve the promise, trust, clarity and operational readiness before scaling traffic.</p></article><article><span>03</span><h3>Do not build what a simpler decision can remove.</h3><p>A feature is an operating commitment. Make sure the problem requires it.</p></article><article><span>04</span><h3>Do not publish a number that cannot survive a follow-up question.</h3><p>Scope, baseline, period and source matter more than a large unsupported result.</p></article></div></div></section>

  <section class="section facts-section"><div class="wrap facts-grid"><div><span class="eyebrow">Education</span><h3>Faculty of Al-Alsun, Ain Shams University</h3><p>Completed two academic years of undergraduate study in languages.</p></div><div><span class="eyebrow">Languages</span><h3>Arabic · Native</h3><p>English · professional written communication and intermediate spoken communication.</p></div><div><span class="eyebrow">Current focus</span><h3>Roles and selected business engagements</h3><p>Customer experience, support operations, process improvement, service quality and business operations.</p></div></div></section>
  <section class="section zone-paper about-cta"><div class="wrap about-cta__inner reveal"><div><span class="eyebrow">The next conversation</span><h2>See the work, or tell me the problem you are trying to solve.</h2></div><div class="cluster"><a class="btn btn--primary" href={withBase('/work')}>View selected work</a><a class="btn btn--ghost" href={withBase('/contact')}>Contact Ahmed</a></div></div></section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero{background:radial-gradient(circle at 80% 30%,rgba(121,183,255,.14),transparent 24rem),var(--night)}.about-hero__grid{position:relative;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.1fr .6fr;gap:clamp(3rem,9vw,8rem);align-items:center}.about-hero h1{margin:1rem 0 1.4rem;font-size:var(--fs-page)}.about-portrait{position:relative;width:min(100%,350px);margin-inline:auto;padding:.6rem;border:1px solid var(--hairline-strong);border-radius:32px 14px 40px 18px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.055);box-shadow:var(--shadow-deep);transform:rotate(1.5deg)}.about-portrait img{width:100%;border-radius:25px 10px 32px 13px}.about-portrait span{position:absolute;left:-2rem;right:2rem;bottom:1.7rem;padding:.8rem 1rem;border:1px solid var(--hairline);border-radius:var(--shape-sm);background:rgba(6,24,34,.82);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);font:750 .62rem var(--font-head)}
  .story-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr .55fr;gap:clamp(3rem,9vw,8rem);align-items:start}.story-copy h2{margin:1rem 0 1.5rem;font-size:var(--fs-h2)}.story-copy p{margin-bottom:1.2rem;color:var(--ink-soft)}.story-principle{position:sticky;top:7rem;padding:2rem;border-radius:64% 36% 57% 43%/42% 62% 38% 58%;background:var(--signal-soft);box-shadow:var(--shadow-soft)}.story-principle blockquote{font:italic 1.65rem/1.35 var(--font-serif)}.story-principle p{margin-top:1.3rem;color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:.82rem}
  .timeline-section{background:var(--night-soft)}.timeline{position:relative;display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:1rem}.timeline::before{content:'';position:absolute;left:4%;right:4%;top:27px;height:2px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--coral),var(--violet),var(--sky),var(--signal))}.timeline article{position:relative;z-index:2;padding:0 1rem}.timeline article::before{content:'';display:block;width:54px;height:54px;margin-bottom:1.5rem;border-radius:52% 48% 43% 57%/48% 58% 42% 52%;background:var(--signal);box-shadow:0 0 0 9px rgba(255,255,255,.04)}.timeline article:nth-child(1)::before{background:var(--coral)}.timeline article:nth-child(2)::before{background:var(--violet)}.timeline article:nth-child(3)::before{background:var(--sky)}.timeline span{color:var(--signal);font:850 .58rem var(--font-head);letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase}.timeline h3{margin:.7rem 0;font-size:1.25rem}.timeline p{color:var(--slate);font-size:.78rem}
  .principle-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem}.principle-grid article{min-height:230px;padding:2rem;border:1px solid var(--paper-line);border-radius:var(--shape-md);background:rgba(255,255,255,.62);box-shadow:var(--shadow-soft)}.principle-grid span{color:var(--signal-deep);font:850 .6rem var(--font-head)}.principle-grid h3{margin:1.6rem 0 .7rem;font-size:1.45rem}.principle-grid p{color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:.82rem}
  .facts-section{background:var(--night)}.facts-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1rem}.facts-grid>div{padding:1.7rem;border-left:2px solid var(--signal)}.facts-grid h3{margin:1rem 0 .6rem;font-size:1.25rem}.facts-grid p{color:var(--slate);font-size:.8rem}.about-cta__inner{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr auto;gap:2rem;align-items:center;padding:clamp(2rem,5vw,4rem);border-radius:var(--shape-lg);background:var(--sky-soft);box-shadow:var(--shadow-soft)}.about-cta h2{max-width:780px;margin-top:.8rem;font-size:var(--fs-h2)}
  @media(max-width:900px){.about-hero__grid,.story-grid,.about-cta__inner{grid-template-columns:1fr}.story-principle{position:relative;top:auto}.timeline{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}.timeline::before{display:none}.principle-grid,.facts-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}.facts-grid>div:last-child{grid-column:1/-1}}
  @media(max-width:560px){.timeline,.principle-grid,.facts-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.facts-grid>div:last-child{grid-column:auto}.about-portrait span{left:.8rem;right:.8rem}}
</style>
